1
00:00:11,860 --> 00:00:12,730
That's all?

2
00:00:12,780 --> 00:00:13,649
Torture him.

3
00:00:13,650 --> 00:00:14,299
No!

4
00:00:14,300 --> 00:00:16,380
Alright. I'll talk.

5
00:00:16,900 --> 00:00:18,289
I'll talk.

6
00:00:18,290 --> 00:00:19,500
Well,

7
00:00:20,020 --> 00:00:21,379
people in the trade all think...

8
00:00:21,380 --> 00:00:22,699
It has nothing to do with me.

9
00:00:22,700 --> 00:00:24,890
I don't think so.

10
00:00:25,540 --> 00:00:27,730
It's just everyone in the trade
thinks you...

11
00:00:28,660 --> 00:00:29,500
Uh...

12
00:00:30,160 --> 00:00:31,960
You stick your nose
into other people's business.

13
00:00:31,960 --> 00:00:35,760
=Cases Between Us=

14
00:00:36,290 --> 00:00:37,899
=Episode 29=
Don't look at him. Look at me.

15
00:00:37,900 --> 00:00:39,650
Please hear me out.

16
00:00:39,690 --> 00:00:40,609
Well,

17
00:00:40,610 --> 00:00:42,139
whenever someone brings in an antique,

18
00:00:42,140 --> 00:00:44,779
the buyer always
comes to you for an appraisal.

19
00:00:44,780 --> 00:00:46,739
After you take one look,
you talk it down to nothing,

20
00:00:46,740 --> 00:00:48,600
and the buyer comes back
demanding a refund.

21
00:00:48,600 --> 00:00:51,690
After that happens a few times,
this is killing our business.

22
00:00:54,930 --> 00:00:56,100
Mr. Zhang.

23
00:00:58,250 --> 00:00:59,860
I'm telling them the truth, right?

24
00:01:02,610 --> 00:01:04,420
Young Master Zhao.

25
00:01:04,970 --> 00:01:08,179
In the antiques business,
real pieces are rare.

26
00:01:08,180 --> 00:01:10,489
Most are fakes.

27
00:01:10,490 --> 00:01:11,489
Your family's affluent.

28
00:01:11,490 --> 00:01:12,379
You don't have to worry.

29
00:01:12,380 --> 00:01:13,899
The rest of us have to make a living.

30
00:01:13,900 --> 00:01:14,969
Right?

31
00:01:14,970 --> 00:01:15,819
Besides,

32
00:01:15,820 --> 00:01:17,129
you grew up surrounded by

33
00:01:17,130 --> 00:01:18,579
imperial treasures.

34
00:01:18,580 --> 00:01:20,939
The only things that catch your eye
are national treasures.

35
00:01:20,940 --> 00:01:22,370
National treasure.

36
00:01:22,410 --> 00:01:24,120
But just because
something doesn't impress you

37
00:01:24,120 --> 00:01:25,340
doesn't mean it's worthless,

38
00:01:26,020 --> 00:01:27,980
to be frank.

39
00:01:34,900 --> 00:01:35,730
Chief.

40
00:01:38,490 --> 00:01:39,810
Not done questioning him?

41
00:01:40,330 --> 00:01:41,659
Mr. Zhao is settling old scores

42
00:01:41,660 --> 00:01:42,930
while he's at it.

43
00:01:45,660 --> 00:01:46,860
Still,

44
00:01:47,130 --> 00:01:48,530
Zhang Baochen did confirm

45
00:01:48,900 --> 00:01:50,379
that Shunzi brought him

46
00:01:50,380 --> 00:01:53,049
the landscape jade inkstone
around 7:30 PM last night.

47
00:01:53,050 --> 00:01:54,539
According to the autopsy,

48
00:01:54,540 --> 00:01:55,769
Ma Yuzhen was killed

49
00:01:55,770 --> 00:01:58,340
between 8 PM and 8:15 PM.

50
00:01:58,380 --> 00:02:00,620
Zhang Baochen's statement
matches Shunzi's.

51
00:02:00,740 --> 00:02:02,170
In that case,

52
00:02:02,380 --> 00:02:03,860
it wasn't Shunzi.

53
00:02:05,540 --> 00:02:07,530
There are two sets of fingerprints
on the hammer.

54
00:02:08,770 --> 00:02:10,049
Shunzi used it for work,

55
00:02:10,050 --> 00:02:11,690
so naturally, his prints are on it.

56
00:02:13,210 --> 00:02:15,220
If he isn't the killer,

57
00:02:18,300 --> 00:02:20,060
then the other set

58
00:02:21,140 --> 00:02:22,970
must belong to the murderer.

59
00:02:24,210 --> 00:02:24,739
Let's go.

60
00:02:24,740 --> 00:02:26,180
- You're leaving?
- I'll see you out.

61
00:02:27,020 --> 00:02:28,179
Stay put.

62
00:02:28,180 --> 00:02:29,259
Stay put.

63
00:02:29,260 --> 00:02:31,090
You scared me.

64
00:02:32,260 --> 00:02:33,049
Hold on.

65
00:02:33,050 --> 00:02:33,859
Young Master Zhao,

66
00:02:33,860 --> 00:02:36,049
I've told you everything I know.

67
00:02:36,050 --> 00:02:37,410
I've been here this long,

68
00:02:38,260 --> 00:02:39,979
can't I at least get a bit to eat?

69
00:02:39,980 --> 00:02:41,979
You kept saying, "Torture him."

70
00:02:41,980 --> 00:02:43,530
Can't you give me some food?

71
00:02:46,140 --> 00:02:47,139
Give him something to eat.

72
00:02:47,140 --> 00:02:48,020
Yes.

73
00:02:53,260 --> 00:02:54,690
Don't try anything silly.

74
00:03:24,020 --> 00:03:26,180
Only two bites?

75
00:03:34,300 --> 00:03:35,489
I lock him up for the night.

76
00:03:35,490 --> 00:03:37,060
That'll teach him a lesson.

77
00:03:37,930 --> 00:03:40,179
What did Zhang Baochen do to you?

78
00:03:40,180 --> 00:03:41,370
You just wouldn't let him off.

79
00:03:41,580 --> 00:03:43,530
Anyone who smuggles national treasures,

80
00:03:43,530 --> 00:03:45,290
I'll hunt them down,
no matter how far they run.

81
00:03:45,290 --> 00:03:48,609
Chief. No. 2 Guangming Elementary School
reported a case.

82
00:03:48,610 --> 00:03:51,370
Chang Fei barged into the school
and beat up one of the teachers.

83
00:03:56,610 --> 00:03:57,299
Name.

84
00:03:57,300 --> 00:03:59,089
(To Rid Evil of the People)

85
00:03:59,090 --> 00:04:00,090
Shi Litai.

86
00:04:02,180 --> 00:04:03,410
Why did you hit him?

87
00:04:03,740 --> 00:04:05,060
Ask him.

88
00:04:05,180 --> 00:04:06,019
He came out of nowhere

89
00:04:06,020 --> 00:04:07,209
and beat me up.

90
00:04:07,210 --> 00:04:08,739
How should I know what got into him?

91
00:04:08,740 --> 00:04:10,019
You're asking me?

92
00:04:10,020 --> 00:04:10,859
You killed Yuzhen,

93
00:04:10,860 --> 00:04:12,580
and now you're playing dumb?

94
00:04:13,520 --> 00:04:14,979
(Shi Litai)
Yuzhen and I

95
00:04:14,980 --> 00:04:16,699
were married for 15 years.

96
00:04:16,700 --> 00:04:17,699
Why would I kill her?

97
00:04:17,700 --> 00:04:18,820
Why?

98
00:04:19,330 --> 00:04:21,259
For her inheritance and insurance money.

99
00:04:21,260 --> 00:04:22,089
Wait.

100
00:04:22,090 --> 00:04:23,170
Hold on.

101
00:04:23,210 --> 00:04:24,140
What was that?

102
00:04:24,580 --> 00:04:27,650
Aren't you Yuzhen's husband?

103
00:04:28,260 --> 00:04:29,169
I...

104
00:04:29,170 --> 00:04:30,140
Um.

105
00:04:32,170 --> 00:04:33,490
That's his fault.

106
00:04:33,580 --> 00:04:35,780
He refused to divorce Yuzhen.

107
00:04:36,900 --> 00:04:38,209
He's nothing but a pretty boy.

108
00:04:38,210 --> 00:04:39,849
- Who are you calling a pretty boy?
- You.

109
00:04:39,850 --> 00:04:40,899
Say that again.

110
00:04:40,900 --> 00:04:41,849
You're a pretty boy.

111
00:04:41,850 --> 00:04:42,619
Say it again.

112
00:04:42,620 --> 00:04:43,899
Chang Fei, listen.

113
00:04:43,900 --> 00:04:44,699
Say it again.

114
00:04:44,700 --> 00:04:46,329
Don't start this in a police station.

115
00:04:46,330 --> 00:04:47,139
I'm a pretty boy?

116
00:04:47,140 --> 00:04:48,059
- You're an old, ugly man.
- So what if I called you that?

117
00:04:48,060 --> 00:04:49,379
Don't start that

118
00:04:49,380 --> 00:04:50,379
in a police station.

119
00:04:50,380 --> 00:04:50,849
Enough.

120
00:04:50,850 --> 00:04:51,900
Let him go.

121
00:04:53,210 --> 00:04:54,050
Get down.

122
00:05:02,530 --> 00:05:03,530
Listen.

123
00:05:03,630 --> 00:05:05,379
You say he committed murder.
Can you prove it?

124
00:05:05,380 --> 00:05:07,019
Of course I do.

125
00:05:07,020 --> 00:05:08,849
The old lady next door

126
00:05:08,850 --> 00:05:11,019
saw Shi Litai running out

127
00:05:11,020 --> 00:05:12,139
of the second floor

128
00:05:12,140 --> 00:05:13,850
before I brought the police back.

129
00:05:14,730 --> 00:05:15,580
You!

130
00:05:18,380 --> 00:05:20,850
Where were you
between 7:30 PM and 8:30 PM last night?

131
00:05:21,170 --> 00:05:22,090
I...

132
00:05:23,260 --> 00:05:25,329
I was home having dinner

133
00:05:25,330 --> 00:05:26,289
and reading.

134
00:05:26,290 --> 00:05:27,379
So

135
00:05:27,380 --> 00:05:29,529
you don't have an alibi.

136
00:05:29,530 --> 00:05:30,530
I...

137
00:05:34,290 --> 00:05:35,410
Take his fingerprints.

138
00:05:36,140 --> 00:05:37,169
Come with me, Mr. Shi.

139
00:05:37,170 --> 00:05:37,939
Where are we going?

140
00:05:37,940 --> 00:05:38,699
Fingerprinting.

141
00:05:38,700 --> 00:05:39,490
You...

142
00:05:39,940 --> 00:05:41,259
You can't frame me.

143
00:05:41,260 --> 00:05:42,969
I'm a public school teacher.

144
00:05:42,970 --> 00:05:45,170
I'm a law-abiding citizen.

145
00:05:45,940 --> 00:05:47,460
You can't frame me.

146
00:06:16,970 --> 00:06:18,090
Zhao Shaoshang.

147
00:06:18,620 --> 00:06:19,729
Wan'er,

148
00:06:19,730 --> 00:06:21,089
when did you get here?

149
00:06:21,090 --> 00:06:22,820
You've gotten bold enough

150
00:06:22,970 --> 00:06:24,530
to disappear on me now.

151
00:06:24,700 --> 00:06:26,579
What are you talking about? Disappear?

152
00:06:26,580 --> 00:06:28,939
I've been busy keeping the capital safe.

153
00:06:28,940 --> 00:06:29,699
You know what?

154
00:06:29,700 --> 00:06:31,169
There was a murder.

155
00:06:31,170 --> 00:06:33,650
I haven't had a proper rest in days.
I have dark circles now.

156
00:06:34,700 --> 00:06:36,290
So busy that you haven't even gone home?

157
00:06:36,380 --> 00:06:37,410
No.

158
00:06:44,530 --> 00:06:45,610
Come here.

159
00:06:46,580 --> 00:06:47,780
I'm not.

160
00:06:47,940 --> 00:06:48,900
One.

161
00:06:49,410 --> 00:06:50,650
We're in the police station now.

162
00:06:51,260 --> 00:06:51,819
Two.

163
00:06:51,820 --> 00:06:53,259
Have some sense.

164
00:06:53,260 --> 00:06:54,140
Three.

165
00:06:57,090 --> 00:06:58,050
What?

166
00:07:00,090 --> 00:07:00,969
You're hurt.

167
00:07:00,970 --> 00:07:01,939
No.

168
00:07:01,940 --> 00:07:02,940
I'm fine.

169
00:07:03,410 --> 00:07:06,649
Easy. Are you trying to kill your brother?

170
00:07:06,650 --> 00:07:07,970
Chief Yuan.

171
00:07:08,020 --> 00:07:09,940
My brother is only
an investigative consultant.

172
00:07:09,970 --> 00:07:11,240
He doesn't draw a salary.

173
00:07:11,240 --> 00:07:13,169
Why did you send him
on dangerous field assignments?

174
00:07:13,170 --> 00:07:15,260
Is the police station that short-handed?

175
00:07:15,410 --> 00:07:16,380
Wait.

176
00:07:16,480 --> 00:07:17,520
Don't blame Yuan Hong.

177
00:07:17,520 --> 00:07:18,849
I scraped myself

178
00:07:18,850 --> 00:07:20,650
while training the dog.

179
00:07:24,210 --> 00:07:25,700
I twisted a bit.

180
00:07:27,140 --> 00:07:28,290
And

181
00:07:33,500 --> 00:07:36,050
ran into something sharp.

182
00:07:37,210 --> 00:07:38,290
What?

183
00:07:40,060 --> 00:07:41,850
A dagger.

184
00:07:45,330 --> 00:07:47,560
It's not serious.
Ask Yuan Hong if you don't believe me.

185
00:07:47,560 --> 00:07:48,019
Yuan Hong.

186
00:07:48,020 --> 00:07:48,970
Tell her.

187
00:07:52,170 --> 00:07:54,089
Du Wenjiu cleaned and bandaged it.

188
00:07:54,090 --> 00:07:56,159
He said it missed the artery
by two centimeters.

189
00:07:56,159 --> 00:07:58,969
As long as he changes the dressing regularly,
he should recover completely.

190
00:07:58,969 --> 00:08:00,259
Why did you tell her everything?

191
00:08:00,260 --> 00:08:00,939
See?

192
00:08:00,940 --> 00:08:02,290
It's nothing.

193
00:08:02,330 --> 00:08:03,619
Just a scratch.

194
00:08:03,620 --> 00:08:05,140
What if next time

195
00:08:05,700 --> 00:08:07,260
it's two centimeters closer?

196
00:08:07,820 --> 00:08:09,780
It would hit the artery, wouldn't it?

197
00:08:10,410 --> 00:08:12,090
It would be serious, wouldn't it?

198
00:08:23,820 --> 00:08:25,090
There won't be a next time.

199
00:08:25,650 --> 00:08:26,530
I promise.

200
00:08:32,650 --> 00:08:33,409
See?

201
00:08:33,410 --> 00:08:34,099
He promised.

202
00:08:34,100 --> 00:08:34,769
Right?

203
00:08:34,770 --> 00:08:36,499
Remember
what the fortune-teller told Mother?

204
00:08:36,500 --> 00:08:38,319
I'm protected by the divine.
I'm the chosen one.

205
00:08:38,319 --> 00:08:39,660
I'll be fine. Wan'er.

206
00:08:40,100 --> 00:08:41,130
Chief.

207
00:08:42,410 --> 00:08:43,929
We found a briefcase
at Shi Litai's house.

208
00:08:43,930 --> 00:08:45,540
There was a bloodstained earring inside.

209
00:08:45,620 --> 00:08:46,730
It belongs to Ma Yuzhen.

210
00:08:47,690 --> 00:08:48,850
It's a lead.

211
00:08:48,860 --> 00:08:51,019
Well, I've got to question the suspect.
We'll talk later.

212
00:08:51,020 --> 00:08:52,809
- If Father asks, tell him I went back to school.
- Zhao Shaoshang.

213
00:08:52,810 --> 00:08:53,940
I'm staying in the dorm.

214
00:09:04,260 --> 00:09:05,370
Don't worry.

215
00:09:05,930 --> 00:09:07,180
I give you my word.

216
00:09:07,450 --> 00:09:09,130
I won't let him get hurt again.

217
00:09:16,880 --> 00:09:17,919
Officer,

218
00:09:17,920 --> 00:09:19,619
I'm innocent.

219
00:09:19,620 --> 00:09:22,090
Someone's trying to set me up.

220
00:09:22,100 --> 00:09:23,809
The briefcase is mine,

221
00:09:23,810 --> 00:09:25,420
but I didn't take

222
00:09:25,530 --> 00:09:27,540
(Jingshi Police Department, Evidence)
the earrings.

223
00:09:28,110 --> 00:09:29,199
Your fingerprints

224
00:09:29,200 --> 00:09:30,890
match the ones on the murder weapon.

225
00:09:31,100 --> 00:09:32,220
And you say you're innocent?

226
00:09:34,220 --> 00:09:35,010
Uh...

227
00:09:36,740 --> 00:09:37,970
Ma Buyan.

228
00:09:38,400 --> 00:09:40,529
It had to be Ma Buyan trying to frame me.

229
00:09:40,530 --> 00:09:42,770
I met with him last night

230
00:09:42,840 --> 00:09:44,180
before I went to the shop.

231
00:09:50,290 --> 00:09:51,420
Buyan.

232
00:09:52,900 --> 00:09:54,340
Litai.

233
00:09:56,320 --> 00:10:00,040
(Ma Buyan)

234
00:10:00,670 --> 00:10:03,100
You're heading out to gamble again?

235
00:10:12,220 --> 00:10:13,060
You...

236
00:10:13,220 --> 00:10:15,289
Why did you take that out?

237
00:10:15,290 --> 00:10:16,769
Would your sister approve?

238
00:10:16,770 --> 00:10:19,339
I put something in her food.

239
00:10:19,340 --> 00:10:20,099
She's asleep.

240
00:10:20,100 --> 00:10:20,569
You...

241
00:10:20,570 --> 00:10:21,859
(Noodle Shop)

242
00:10:21,860 --> 00:10:23,529
It's a family heirloom.

243
00:10:23,530 --> 00:10:25,339
It'll be mine someday.

244
00:10:25,340 --> 00:10:26,379
It's mine.

245
00:10:26,380 --> 00:10:27,529
Stay out of it.

246
00:10:27,530 --> 00:10:28,460
Buyan.

247
00:10:28,650 --> 00:10:29,459
Buyan.

248
00:10:29,460 --> 00:10:30,850
You can't sell that.

249
00:10:31,650 --> 00:10:32,420
Move.

250
00:10:34,530 --> 00:10:35,619
You ungrateful brat.

251
00:10:35,620 --> 00:10:37,660
You'll ruin this family one day!

252
00:10:38,930 --> 00:10:40,809
I was worried about Yuzhen,

253
00:10:40,810 --> 00:10:42,820
so I went to check on her.

254
00:10:44,900 --> 00:10:46,339
But the moment I walked in,

255
00:10:46,340 --> 00:10:47,940
someone knocked me out.

256
00:10:48,720 --> 00:10:50,100
When I came to,

257
00:10:50,600 --> 00:10:52,390
Yuzhen was dead.

258
00:10:54,440 --> 00:10:56,019
I panicked and ran.

259
00:10:56,020 --> 00:10:57,300
You ran away?

260
00:10:57,740 --> 00:10:59,019
Why didn't you call the police?

261
00:10:59,020 --> 00:11:00,899
I was afraid no one would believe me.

262
00:11:00,900 --> 00:11:01,569
I...

263
00:11:01,570 --> 00:11:03,660
I'm the one being framed now.

264
00:11:03,980 --> 00:11:04,729
Buyan

265
00:11:04,730 --> 00:11:06,449
did this on purpose.

266
00:11:06,450 --> 00:11:07,409
He knew

267
00:11:07,410 --> 00:11:08,909
I'd come see his sister,

268
00:11:08,910 --> 00:11:10,979
then circled back and killed her.

269
00:11:10,980 --> 00:11:12,850
That way I'd take the fall,

270
00:11:13,050 --> 00:11:15,529
and he'd get all the insurance money.

271
00:11:15,530 --> 00:11:17,180
Buyan's missing.

272
00:11:18,290 --> 00:11:19,409
That's impossible.

273
00:11:19,410 --> 00:11:20,929
We've been looking for him

274
00:11:20,930 --> 00:11:22,850
since the murder.

275
00:11:23,140 --> 00:11:24,049
He wasn't home.

276
00:11:24,050 --> 00:11:25,770
He's probably at a gambling house.

277
00:11:26,100 --> 00:11:27,770
I know where he is.

278
00:11:31,570 --> 00:11:32,420
Wan'er,

279
00:11:32,570 --> 00:11:34,300
I need a favor.

280
00:11:34,410 --> 00:11:36,049
What are you up to now?

281
00:11:36,050 --> 00:11:37,970
Didn't you already catch the killer?

282
00:11:38,290 --> 00:11:40,139
Shi Litai has been cleared.

283
00:11:40,140 --> 00:11:42,760
He has myasthenia gravis.
He couldn't have used the murder weapon.

284
00:11:42,860 --> 00:11:43,979
Our prime suspect now

285
00:11:43,980 --> 00:11:45,420
is Yuzhen's younger brother.

286
00:11:46,220 --> 00:11:48,499
But the gambling house is holding him.

287
00:11:48,500 --> 00:11:49,859
The owner

288
00:11:49,860 --> 00:11:52,460
just so happens to be a broker.

289
00:11:52,690 --> 00:11:54,180
And he just so happens

290
00:11:54,260 --> 00:11:57,660
to want your new Patek Philippe.

291
00:11:58,980 --> 00:12:01,220
Zhao Shaoshang,

292
00:12:01,290 --> 00:12:02,979
do you know how hard it was for me

293
00:12:02,980 --> 00:12:05,169
to get that watch?

294
00:12:05,170 --> 00:12:05,929
I know.

295
00:12:05,930 --> 00:12:09,219
That's why it's worth so much.

296
00:12:09,220 --> 00:12:11,850
Think of it as a sacrifice for the people

297
00:12:11,930 --> 00:12:13,660
and for justice.

298
00:12:13,900 --> 00:12:15,890
For justice?

299
00:12:16,770 --> 00:12:19,660
You sure know how to side with outsiders.

300
00:12:30,120 --> 00:12:31,129
Just that watch?

301
00:12:31,130 --> 00:12:32,340
Just that one.

302
00:12:34,620 --> 00:12:35,700
I'll give it to you.

303
00:12:36,220 --> 00:12:37,940
- But I have one condition.
- Name it.

304
00:12:39,860 --> 00:12:41,169
This is your last case

305
00:12:41,170 --> 00:12:42,049
with the police.

306
00:12:42,050 --> 00:12:44,820
Once it's solved, you're going home.
You're quitting the police force.

307
00:12:45,100 --> 00:12:46,339
That's a bit much.

308
00:12:46,340 --> 00:12:47,449
Deal or not?

309
00:12:47,450 --> 00:12:48,139
Zhao Wan'er.

310
00:12:48,140 --> 00:12:49,300
Deal.

311
00:12:54,740 --> 00:12:55,490
Very well.

312
00:13:01,380 --> 00:13:02,619
Why did you agree to

313
00:13:02,620 --> 00:13:03,890
such an outrageous demand?

314
00:13:06,170 --> 00:13:07,379
It's just a stopgap.

315
00:13:07,380 --> 00:13:08,580
You taught me that.

316
00:13:11,620 --> 00:13:12,970
Stopgap?

317
00:13:39,450 --> 00:13:40,660
The ledger.

318
00:13:43,220 --> 00:13:44,460
I left it somewhere.

319
00:13:49,410 --> 00:13:51,169
I've told you everything I know.

320
00:13:51,170 --> 00:13:53,010
Why are you still coming to me?

321
00:13:56,340 --> 00:13:57,340
Let me ask you something.

322
00:13:57,810 --> 00:13:59,929
Canglong House is
one of the biggest jade dealers around.

323
00:13:59,930 --> 00:14:01,289
You and the Ma's Jade Shop

324
00:14:01,290 --> 00:14:02,850
are competitors, aren't you?

325
00:14:05,500 --> 00:14:07,770
Why are you looking at me? He's asking you.

326
00:14:08,900 --> 00:14:09,409
Officer,

327
00:14:09,410 --> 00:14:11,099
the Ma's Jade Shop

328
00:14:11,100 --> 00:14:12,859
only deals in jade.

329
00:14:12,860 --> 00:14:14,529
I deal in all kinds of antiques.

330
00:14:14,530 --> 00:14:16,019
I wouldn't call us competitors.

331
00:14:16,020 --> 00:14:20,660
Though we've had a few run-ins.

332
00:14:20,740 --> 00:14:23,499
I heard you and Master Ma
had a fight a few years ago.

333
00:14:23,500 --> 00:14:24,289
He threw the punches.

334
00:14:24,290 --> 00:14:25,339
I never hit back.

335
00:14:25,340 --> 00:14:26,700
The police even showed up.

336
00:14:26,860 --> 00:14:28,420
But they did nothing.

337
00:14:28,620 --> 00:14:30,730
- They probably took a payoff.
- Cut the crap.

338
00:14:31,650 --> 00:14:33,010
Why did he hit you?

339
00:14:33,930 --> 00:14:34,529
It was all over

340
00:14:34,530 --> 00:14:36,940
that heirloom jade pendant.

341
00:14:37,100 --> 00:14:38,139
A few years back,

342
00:14:38,140 --> 00:14:39,769
a broker came to me.

343
00:14:39,770 --> 00:14:43,219
He wanted me
to introduce a Japanese buyer.

344
00:14:43,220 --> 00:14:44,499
The buyer wanted that pendant.

345
00:14:44,500 --> 00:14:45,610
A Japanese buyer?

346
00:14:46,170 --> 00:14:47,099
Masashige Kobayashi.

347
00:14:47,100 --> 00:14:47,979
Right.

348
00:14:47,980 --> 00:14:48,289
Do you

349
00:14:48,290 --> 00:14:49,540
know him?

350
00:14:51,100 --> 00:14:52,660
What did I tell you?

351
00:14:54,770 --> 00:14:56,420
National treasures are not for sale.

352
00:14:57,770 --> 00:15:00,649
But it wasn't a national treasure.
Let's at least be reasonable.

353
00:15:00,650 --> 00:15:01,449
Enough.

354
00:15:01,450 --> 00:15:02,490
Go on.

355
00:15:04,380 --> 00:15:06,769
I don't know who told the Japanese
that the blood jade pendant

356
00:15:06,770 --> 00:15:09,360
could ward off evil and misfortune.

357
00:15:09,360 --> 00:15:11,080
He searched all
over Liulichang Antique Market

358
00:15:11,080 --> 00:15:12,799
and eventually set his sights
on the Ma family.

359
00:15:12,799 --> 00:15:14,859
He demanded the best.

360
00:15:14,860 --> 00:15:16,099
Who would sell a family heirloom

361
00:15:16,100 --> 00:15:17,449
unless they were desperate?

362
00:15:17,450 --> 00:15:19,809
Exactly.

363
00:15:19,810 --> 00:15:22,529
But he kept pushing me
to talk to the Ma family.

364
00:15:22,530 --> 00:15:24,859
I went several times.
In the end, we got into a fight. Right?

365
00:15:24,860 --> 00:15:25,929
Master Ma really

366
00:15:25,930 --> 00:15:26,899
could throw a punch.

367
00:15:26,900 --> 00:15:28,219
He hit me in the face,

368
00:15:28,220 --> 00:15:28,809
and my glasses

369
00:15:28,810 --> 00:15:30,540
flew off.

370
00:15:31,980 --> 00:15:33,180
These are new ones?

371
00:15:33,410 --> 00:15:34,979
They sure make your eyes look bigger.

372
00:15:34,980 --> 00:15:36,220
Look decent, do I?

373
00:15:37,220 --> 00:15:38,049
Then?

374
00:15:38,050 --> 00:15:39,449
That was it.

375
00:15:39,450 --> 00:15:40,379
He wouldn't sell.

376
00:15:40,380 --> 00:15:42,529
What was I supposed to do? Rob him?

377
00:15:42,530 --> 00:15:43,859
So you held a grudge?

378
00:15:43,860 --> 00:15:44,499
No.

379
00:15:44,500 --> 00:15:45,409
No. Absolutely not.

380
00:15:45,410 --> 00:15:46,340
No.

381
00:15:46,650 --> 00:15:48,049
Business

382
00:15:48,050 --> 00:15:50,610
isn't won with fists.

383
00:15:51,100 --> 00:15:52,540
Then what wins it?

384
00:15:54,220 --> 00:15:56,409
You already know.

385
00:15:56,410 --> 00:15:57,619
Connections.

386
00:15:57,620 --> 00:15:59,300
Money.

387
00:15:59,450 --> 00:16:00,890
Resources.

388
00:16:01,260 --> 00:16:02,169
And people like you.

389
00:16:02,170 --> 00:16:03,049
Back to the point.

390
00:16:03,050 --> 00:16:04,250
Come here.

391
00:16:04,620 --> 00:16:05,739
Tell me.

392
00:16:05,740 --> 00:16:06,649
Ma Buyan's missing.

393
00:16:06,650 --> 00:16:07,850
Do you know anything about it?

394
00:16:10,380 --> 00:16:11,649
Since when?

395
00:16:11,650 --> 00:16:12,529
I...

396
00:16:12,530 --> 00:16:13,859
I had nothing to do with it.

397
00:16:13,860 --> 00:16:15,409
I've been home

398
00:16:15,410 --> 00:16:16,529
these past two days.

399
00:16:16,530 --> 00:16:18,529
The account books
are piled up like mountains.

400
00:16:18,530 --> 00:16:20,610
He racked up gambling debts
and got himself kidnapped.

401
00:16:20,620 --> 00:16:24,060
They said it was the broker
who came looking for the pendant.

402
00:16:25,450 --> 00:16:26,850
Miss Qiu?

403
00:16:28,620 --> 00:16:29,499
Officers,

404
00:16:29,500 --> 00:16:30,259
I'm innocent.

405
00:16:30,260 --> 00:16:32,139
I'm just the middleman.

406
00:16:32,140 --> 00:16:34,169
I only introduced them.

407
00:16:34,170 --> 00:16:37,220
I can't interfere with what they do.

408
00:16:46,450 --> 00:16:48,730
How about I put you in contact with them?

409
00:16:53,220 --> 00:16:54,219
Let me introduce.

410
00:16:54,220 --> 00:16:56,300
This is Miss Qiu.

411
00:16:56,620 --> 00:16:59,180
Mr. Kobayashi's right-hand woman.

412
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:01,219
(Miss Qiu)

413
00:17:01,220 --> 00:17:03,090
This is Miss Zhao,

414
00:17:03,100 --> 00:17:05,900
Patek Philippe's VIP customer.

415
00:17:06,450 --> 00:17:07,339
I'm just here

416
00:17:07,340 --> 00:17:09,689
to introduce

417
00:17:09,690 --> 00:17:11,579
the two of you.

418
00:17:11,580 --> 00:17:14,539
Whether a deal is made or not

419
00:17:14,540 --> 00:17:16,140
has nothing to do with me.

420
00:17:16,970 --> 00:17:18,660
Nothing at all.

421
00:17:18,690 --> 00:17:19,169
Ladies,

422
00:17:19,170 --> 00:17:20,770
I'll give you a toast.

423
00:17:21,100 --> 00:17:22,010
Well then.

424
00:17:23,490 --> 00:17:24,999
Ladies, I'll leave you two to it.

425
00:17:25,170 --> 00:17:26,860
I'll stay out of your hair.

426
00:17:27,060 --> 00:17:28,010
Enjoy your time.

427
00:17:33,400 --> 00:17:34,409
Miss Zhao.

428
00:17:34,410 --> 00:17:35,619
The new Patek Philippe

429
00:17:35,620 --> 00:17:37,309
124824.

430
00:17:37,310 --> 00:17:38,380
Do you have one in stock?

431
00:17:39,450 --> 00:17:40,490
Wan'er?

432
00:17:41,300 --> 00:17:43,010
You're eating here too?

433
00:17:45,300 --> 00:17:47,460
This lady must be your friend, right?

434
00:17:47,520 --> 00:17:48,739
Mr. Zhao.

435
00:17:48,740 --> 00:17:49,620
Chief Yuan.

436
00:17:50,010 --> 00:17:53,010
If you've got something to say,
just say it. Can we drop the act?

437
00:17:59,190 --> 00:18:02,290
Looks like there's nothing
you want from me.

438
00:18:02,340 --> 00:18:03,539
I'll be on my way.

439
00:18:03,540 --> 00:18:04,660
Goodbye.

440
00:18:05,300 --> 00:18:06,700
One moment, Miss Qiu.

441
00:18:08,780 --> 00:18:09,779
Hunter case.

442
00:18:09,780 --> 00:18:11,259
Split-seconds chronograph movement.

443
00:18:11,260 --> 00:18:13,250
One in yellow gold, one in rose gold.

444
00:18:13,340 --> 00:18:14,490
Which one would you like?

445
00:18:51,120 --> 00:18:54,180
(End of Episode 29)

446
00:18:54,601 --> 00:18:56,241
♪Side by side,
we journey through this life♪

447
00:18:56,241 --> 00:18:57,781
♪Troubled times
are but a laughing matter♪

448
00:18:57,781 --> 00:18:59,031
♪However, the world changes♪

449
00:18:59,031 --> 00:19:00,951
♪You'll still be by my side♪

450
00:19:00,951 --> 00:19:02,641
♪Side by side,
we journey through this life♪

451
00:19:02,641 --> 00:19:04,211
♪Praise and blame come and go♪

452
00:19:04,211 --> 00:19:05,781
♪If this is my final chapter♪

453
00:19:05,781 --> 00:19:08,281
♪I'll solve this mystery with you♪
